            <a:r>
              <a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/>
              <a:t>This is honestly where enterprise deals live or die. LangFuse is great for debugging but not an audit log. Five show-stoppers. One, cost attribution — we can't answer &quot;what's this request cost?&quot; or &quot;who's our biggest spender?&quot; Two, immutable audit log — enterprise auditors need proof that tool X wasn't called by user Y on date Z. Traces don't cut it. Three, PII — raw user input hits disk with no scanning, that's a GDPR violation. Four, model governance — anyone can swap the LLM via env var, needs approval workflow. Five, red-teaming — we should be running OWASP Top 10 adversarial tests nightly.</a:t>
            </a:r>
